The paper also involves probability theory and stochastic processes, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.PF (Probability and Statistics). Additionally, the paper deals with control systems and decision-making, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The Laplace-Stieltjes transform is a mathematical tool used in signal processing and information theory, which could classify the paper under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) since some of the scheduling policies discussed involve learning and adapting to job characteristics.
